    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Altars used at religious sites for liquid offerings, which are poured over it, often through rhytons. These may slope down toward a basin to collect the liquid, or have carved depressions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
